Diagnosis.
Male sternite VIII partially hiding subgenital plates. Male pygofer (
Figs 51, 52
) commonly with short, thin process on dorsal margin at base; ventral margin with tuft of hair-like setae; posterior margin with or without rounded protrusion near apex of pygofer. Subgenital plate (
Fig. 9
) with hair-like setae on external margin. Style (
Fig. 33
) with conspicuous protrusion on ventral margin near base of blade. Aedeagus (
Figs 12
, 
34
) with apodemal processes; shaft elongate, with or without processes at mid-length or subapically; apex membranous.

Coloration.
Head and thorax (
Figs 69, 71
) yellow or brown. Head (
Fig. 1
) frequently with pair of black spots behind ocelli. Pronotum (
Fig. 23
) frequently with small maculae near anterior margin. Forewings (
Fig. 4
) commonly with small black maculae on corium and apex of anal veins, with or without larger black maculae on costal margin at mid-length of wing.
